[[File:kurikarafudouji hououden.jpg|thumb|250px|Phoenix Hall]]

'''Kurikara Fudō-ji''' (倶利迦羅不動寺) is a temple of {{ill|Koyasan Shingon Buddhism|ja|高野山真言宗|12=draft}}, designated as a Bekkaku Honzan, located in {{ill|Ishikawa Prefecture|ja|石川県|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kahoku District|ja|河北郡|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tsubata Town|ja|津幡町|12=draft}}, and in the area known as {{ill|Kurikara|ja|倶利伽羅 (津幡町)|lt=Kurikara|lt_ja=倶利伽羅|12=draft}}.<ref group="注">Although some sources record the name as “倶利'''伽'''羅不動寺” in accordance with local usage, the official website consistently uses “倶利'''迦'''羅不動寺”.</ref>

==概要==
{{節スタブ}}
'''Kurikara''' is derived from the Sanskrit {{ill|Sanskrit|ja|サンスクリット|12=draft}} word “kulihah”. It means “the black dragon of complete fortune and virtue” and comes from the name of the principal image, in which a sword is entwined by a {{ill|Black Dragon|ja|黒龍|12=draft}}.<ref>{{Cite web|和書|url=http://www.kurikara.or.jp/history/index.html|title=About Kurikara Fudō-ji|publisher=Kurikara Fudō-ji|accessdate=2018-07-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Celebration Ceremony for the 1300th Foundation Year|newspaper=Hokkoku Shimbun|date=2018-04-29|page=28}}</ref>

==歴史==
* In the 2nd year of {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老|12=draft}} (718), it is said that Kurikara Fudō Myōō was enshrined by the imperial command of {{ill|Genshō Tennō|ja|元正天皇|12=draft}}.
* In the 2nd year of {{ill|Kōnin|ja|弘仁|12=draft}} (812), {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|12=draft}} (Kōbō Daishi) carved a Fudō-son statue identical to the principal image and established Chōraku-ji as a head temple.
* In the 24th year of {{ill|Shōwa|ja|昭和|12=draft}} (1949), temple buildings were reconstructed on the site of the Chōraku-ji ruins, and the temple was restored as Kurikara Fudō-ji.

[[File:Oman Jizo (Kurikara).jpg|thumb|人柱となった地元の少女を祀る「おまん地蔵」]]

== Cultural Properties ==
=== 絵画 ===
* Arhat statue: Designated Cultural Property of {{ill|Tsubata Town|ja|津幡町|12=draft}}
* Eleven-faced Kannon Bodhisattva statue: Designated Cultural Property of {{ill|Tsubata Town|ja|津幡町|12=draft}}

=== 古文書 ===
* Letters of Minamoto no Yoritomo: Designated Cultural Property of {{ill|Tsubata Town|ja|津幡町|12=draft}}

=== 史跡 ===
* Nanono Tomb Group (Graves 2, 3, 4): Historic Site of {{ill|Tsubata Town|ja|津幡町|12=draft}}

== アクセス==
* Mountain Top Main Hall
** 20 minutes by car from {{ill|IR Ishikawa Railway|ja|IRいしかわ鉄道|12=draft}} {{ill|Tsubata Station|ja|津幡駅|12=draft}}
** 20 minutes by car from {{ill|Hokuriku Expressway|ja|北陸自動車道|12=draft}} {{ill|Koyabe Interchange|ja|小矢部インターチェンジ|lt=Koyabe IC|lt_ja=小矢部IC|12=draft}}
** 40 minutes by car from {{ill|Hokuriku Expressway|ja|北陸自動車道|12=draft}} {{ill|Kanazawa Higashi Interchange|ja|金沢東インターチェンジ|lt=Kanazawa Higashi IC|lt_ja=金沢東IC|12=draft}}
* Phoenix Hall
** 15 minutes by car from {{ill|IR Ishikawa Railway|ja|IRいしかわ鉄道|12=draft}} {{ill|Tsubata Station|ja|津幡駅|12=draft}}
** 30 minutes by car from {{ill|Hokuriku Expressway|ja|北陸自動車道|12=draft}} {{ill|Koyabe Interchange|ja|小矢部インターチェンジ|lt=Koyabe IC|lt_ja=小矢部IC|12=draft}}
** 30 minutes by car from {{ill|Hokuriku Expressway|ja|北陸自動車道|12=draft}} {{ill|Kanazawa Higashi Interchange|ja|金沢東インターチェンジ|lt=Kanazawa Higashi IC|lt_ja=金沢東IC|12=draft}}

